      {
        "level": "1",
        "name": "Siren's Call",
        "castTime": "Action",
        "range": "Self",
        "concentration": false,
        "ritual": false,
        "material": false,
        "effect": "A warning cry blasts creatures in a cone for 2d8 Thunder damage and pushes them away on a failed Constitution save.",
        "details": "Through the echoes, your call for help shall be heard. A defensive spell created by the magic researchers of the Aeternia kingdom. As you cry for help, you forcefully push away those who mean you harm. However, be mindful, as sound transfers differently under water.\n\nOn Land. Each creature within a 15-foot cone makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, they take 2d8 Thunder damage and are pushed away from you by 5 feet. On a successful save, they take half the damage and are not pushed. Your call travels over 100 feet on land.\n\nUnder Water. Each creature within a 20-foot cone makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, they take 2d8 Thunder damage and are pushed away from you by 15 feet. On a successful save, they take half the damage and are not pushed. Your call travels over 300 feet through water.\n\nHigher-Level Spell Slot. The damage increases by 1d8 for each spell slot level above 1.",
        "open": false,
        "sourceId": "mb-sirens-call",
        "source": "Mythical Blue - The Great Depth",
